content.description: start on juggy lay back crack, climb up through cool moves on small edges
content.location: on the obvious vertical wall between the cave boulder and the parking lot

content.description: Sit start, left hand on a crimp around the left of the arete and right hand on the sloper pinch of the arete (the same start as Pharaoh Arete). Pounce up to a good edge, then set up for a hard move out left. Compress to the top.
Stand start with left hand on the crimp on the overhanging face and right on the Arete. Climb up avoiding all the jugs around the arete. Very fun for being an eliminate.
content.location: Left side of the point down boulder.

content.description: Stand Start on a good side pull. Climb up the Arete/Face using all the good holds.
content.location: Left side/Arete on the Point Down Boulder

content.description: This is what the guide calls Point Down Center. Start from a matched crimp about chest height, a hard start position gives way to crimps (and one fun crimp pinch!) to the top. Several ways to do it. For variety you can easily move over to Pharaoh Left.The guide gives this v0 but the first move feels much harder.
content.location: Point Down Boulder. The crimp rail directly above the "point" of the boulder.

content.description: Start hands matched on a good crimp closer to the left side of the boulder. Move up through crimps and a pinch to the lip.
content.location: Below the Cave boulder in the middle-left of the Pharoah boulder.

content.description:
Sit start in the middle of the Pharaoh Boulder on two good crimps next to each other. Move up and right through crimps to the lip. 

  No eliminations/all holds are on.
content.protection: One pad and a spotter are good. Safe landing, rocks are not much in play.
content.location: Sit start at two crimps in the middle of the Pharaoh Boulder, below the Cave Boulder.

content.description: This problem sit starts on a sidepull pinch/sloper jug at the left of the Pharaoh Boulder. I believe that the large crimp sidepull about 6 feet from the ground around the right of the arete, and the large shelf at about 7-8 on the right side of the arete are not to be used to keep it at it's original grade of V5. I am not sure, however, and welcome any input from other members. I will post pictures when I can get some.
content.protection: Two pads are probably best. Watch your back and head as you head upward.
content.location: Below the Cave Boulder at the far left of the Pharaoh Boulder.

content.description: Start on the Cave Traverse and work left across the rail and stick the crux. Then move up into the undercling of Midget, and finish that topout.
content.protection: Several pads (~3) and a spotter are helpful. The landing is pretty poor and rocky.
content.location: Cave Boulders.

content.description: Sit-Start on underclings below the start to Midget Sit. Do two hard moves into Midget Sit.
content.location: Center of the cave boulder

content.description: Start standing in the center of the cave above the obvious bulge with a slanting left hand crimp and your pick of two right hand holds.  Stand up to the undercling and work straight up.  The blocky jug out left about 3/4 of the way up is off for your hands.
Cool trickery on this problem. Sit start on Midget Sit, traverse low and right and finish on Cave Crack. Low block to the right is off.
content.location: Same start as Midget Sit in the middle of the Cave Boulder. Right hand sloping crimp and left hand around the corner.

content.description: Start sitting in the middle of the Cave Boulder on the obvious bulge with your left hand on a left-facing crimp rail and right hand on the slopey crimper.  Head straight up through several crimpers and an undercling pinch and top it out.  The blocky jug about 3/4 up and to the left is off for your hands.
Very bunchy sit start on underclings. Make a desperate right hand throw to good edge. Work a few small crimps and finish on the the right side of the boulder.
content.location: Down hill from the Cave Boulder and Point Down Boulder.

content.description: Start as for Down Under Right with a scrunched undercling, but follow the line of crimps up and left.
content.location: The little pit below the Point Down boulder.

content.description: Sit start on the far right side, Traverse left staying low, your butt will never be more the 2 feet off the ground.  No top out, "simply" grab the jug on the far left side and you are done.
content.protection: a few pads are required to protect the uneven ground.
content.location: Traverse of the Top Boulder

content.description: Squat start on the shallow arete using a left hand edge and right hand dish pocket (hands are very narrow). Make a long move to a decent edge. Continue straight up with a hard lip encounter.
content.location: Right side of the Cave Boulder.

content.description: Sit start underneath the jugs of Cave Left on an undercling. Paste feet and make a hard deadpoint. There are a few intermediate holds to bump to the jugs. Finish on Cave Left. Crux is not dabbing on the supporting rock or pads.
content.location: Starts below the jugs on the left side of the Cave Boulder.

content.description: Start standing on flat jugs. Work left through a series of incut jugs. Head straight up from there. Mantle is the crux.
content.location: Left side of the Cave Boulder.

content.description: A nice line up the center of the Cave Boulder, to the left of "Midget." Sit start at crimps and move up through a couple of flat/slopey crimps up to good holds and a somewhat spicy/fun topout.
content.protection: Rocky landing, bring 2 pads and a spotter.
content.location: Cave boulders, upper boulder.

content.description: Climb the obvious vertical crack. The lower block to the right is off. Head straight up.
content.location: Right side of the Cave Boulder. Sit start underneath the overhang.

content.description: A rare Minnesota Wisconsin highball. Opposing full-handed sidepulls and heel hooks up a large face. Stand start at opposing side-pulls and head straight up.
content.protection: A bit high and not necessarily "gimme" at the top. Two pads and a spotter are recommended.
content.location:
Actually just up the road from the Cave Boulders. Walk towards the beach along the road about 150 yards and look to the right. The boulder is approximately 100 feet from the road. 

  This will give you a sense of what you're looking for: 

spoiler: vimeo.com/1430978

content.description: Start left on an inverted triangle hold and right on an undercling. With difficulty, pull up and begin slapping up the arete on the left and a choice of sharp edges for the right. Mantle over the right side of the boulder.
content.location: Rightmost side of the Point Down boulder.

content.description: The Cave Boulders consist of two over hanging boulders one higher on the hill then the other, with the top out for the Bottom boulder being the flat space in front of the Top boulder.  The Top boulder is the steeper of the two, and offers the most challenging lines.
